easy 4.5 for 73!!! check out the 40 other reviews on the other  sound board . 5 star on sound quality
- I vacillated a lot before deciding what I think of this one; not only does it have nice quintessential '73 jams, it all just sounds so damn pleasant. A mellow, masterful show.

Wonderful Show! Absolutely love this show. Maybe one of my all time favorites. It has such a wonderful, consistent 'groove' throughout. To me it typified that beautiful '73-'74 jazzy feel the band developed during that time period, highlighted by both individual and collective musical brilliance. Yes, the audio quality is a bit wonky here and there but fuck it! Still a feast for the ears, mind and soul. 
 
Includes absolutely stellar renditions of They Love Each Other (always preferred the fast version), China Cat, I Know You Rider, Playin' in the Band, Here Comes Sunshine, Let it Grow and the creme de la creme, the Eyes of the World!
Exemplar This is the show I played for my son when I wanted to explain how the band could stretch out and take a song to a place where time goes away.   It’s very easy to get lost in this one.
Mind Left Body The "Mind Left Body" in this show is fantastic!!
